column1: Who will win the election for South Carolina's 1st Congressional District in 2020?
column5: ['The Democratic Party candidate', 'The Republican Party candidate', 'Someone else']

column6: Dems get the edge again, but barely here.

New 538 model gives 55 to Democrat. If you go to polls only it favors the Republican. I'll give the Dem the slight advantage. https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2020-election-forecast/house/south-carolina/1/
This is going to be interesting.

Moving up Dems chances due mostly to Lindsey Graham's recent reactions to historic fundraising records of his opponent and large swings in Senate seat polling. If Dems turn up on election day, this seat should stay blue.
Nothing changed here with Democrats having a sizable edge due to demographics.

Polls are old, district leans red but the national polling leans blue. The old polls lean slightly red. I think this one is pretty even but I'm leaning Republican just based on district history and decision desk forecast. This one will need updated once we get more polling. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_congressional_delegations_from_South_Carolina https://forecast.decisiondeskhq.com/house/H2020SC01

Incumbent Cunningham won by around 4,000 votes in 2018, which was considered an upset. He lost four of the five counties in the district but got enough support in the Charleston area to pull his campaign over the finish line. It was a historic win, but in many ways it could be deemed a fluke and was not nearly demanding enough to suggest he is a sure thing this time around. Before him, Republicans had kept the seat since 1980, meaning the district is not blue. It has also swung red in every election since 2000, including both of Obama's terms, suggesting that it is not historically purple either. The Dems have an incumbent advantage here and a substantially larger war chest, but I hesitate to predict that means they've secured the win this early.

Another seat democrats flipped that has little chance of flipping back. The district has a high minority population, majority female and college educated people. None of which are Trump backers. Dems keep it.
